lead_paragraph: British 13th seed Johanna Konta felt "embarrassed" after recovering from a health scare at a humid U.S. Open on Wednesday to claim her place in the third round with a 6-2 5-7 6-2 win over Bulgaria's Tsvetana Pironkova.

headline.print_headline: Konta Collapses on Court but Reaches Third Round
